Standard Recurrence for Modular Inverses. Start from the division identity:

MOD = ⌊MOD/i⌋ * i + (MOD % i)
0 ≡ ⌊MOD/i⌋ * i + (MOD % i)  (mod MOD)
i ≡ −(MOD % i) / ⌊MOD/i⌋  (mod MOD)
1/i ≡ −⌊MOD/i⌋ / (MOD % i)  (mod MOD)

So inv[i] = −⌊MOD/i⌋ * inv[MOD % i].

Then, inv[i] = (MOD-MOD/i) * inv[MOD%i]

The reason it works as a DP: (MOD % i) < i, so inv[MOD % i] is always already computed when reaching i.